SUMMARY:Comprehensive Plan Office Hours- Magnolia Public Library
DESCRIPTION:From the Office of Councilman Kettle: \nRight now\, the Office of Planning and Community Development is putting together four specific subarea plans: the Downtown Regional Plan\, the Northgate plan\, and two Manufacturing-Industrial Center plans. All of these plans are intended to come to Council to be voted on in late summer-early fall\, and you can sign up here for OPCD updates. \nIn the meantime\, my office will be hosting several Comprehensive Plan-specific office hours in March and April. \nThese office hours will follow our standard rules: sign in\, each speaker / group gets 10-15 minutes (depending on how many people have signed up)\, and will be first come\, first serve. \nYou can use my Instagram or Facebook to track updates.
URL:https://discovermagnolia.org/event/comprehensive-plan-office-hours-magnolia-public-library/
LOCATION:Magnolia Public Library\, 2801 34th Ave W\, Seattle\, WA\, 98199\, United States
CATEGORIES:Public Information Sharing
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://discovermagnolia.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Comprehensive-Plan-Office-Hours.png
END:VEVENT
